-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu Nov 06, 2014 06:19AM EST
-- None



Nov 6 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Thursday:

** Cable & Wireless Communications PLC <CWC.L> said it would buy Columbus Intl, a privately-owned fibre-based telecoms provider in the Caribbean, Central America and Andean region, for $1.85 billion to boost its mobile, fixed line, broadband and TV offer. John Malone will have about 13 pct of C&W stock after the deal. [ID:nL6N0SW1W7] [ID:nL6N0SW2EJ]  ** Temasek Holdings Ltd is exiting STATS ChipPAC <STTS.SI> through a $1.8 billion deal with China's Jiangsu Changjiang Electronics Technology Co Ltd <600584.SS> as the Singapore state investor makes room in its portfolio for more global purchases. [ID:nL4N0SW488]  ** Germany's Continental <CONG.DE> is unable to complete its 1.4 billion euros ($1.75 billion) acquisition of U.S. rubber firm Veyance Technologies and may need to sell one of the target company's divisions to win U.S. regulatory approval, Bilanz magazine reported on Thursday. [ID:nL6N0SW30V]  ** Australian engineering firm UGL Ltd <UGL.AX> finalised the years-long $1.1 billion sale of its DTZ property arm to U.S. private equity giant TPG Capital Management LP [TPG.UL]. [ID:nL4N0SV93T]  ** The Finnish government's investment arm Solidium has sold a stake of 2.3 percent in Swedish mobile operator TeliaSonera AB <TLSN.ST> to institutional investors. The sale of the 100 million shares was at a discount of 2.85 percent to the stock's last closing price, and raised 5.04 billion Swedish crowns ($683.6 million). [ID:nL6N0SW36G]  ** British restaurant chain Prezzo Plc <PRZ.L> has agreed to a 303.7 million pounds ($485.4 million) cash bid by U.S. private equity firm TPG <TPG.UL> which values the business at almost 10 times its core earnings. [ID:nL4N0SW3ZP]  ** Four banks including Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp are expected to participate in the second round of bidding for Citigroup Inc's <C.N> unprofitable consumer banking business in Japan, bankers with knowledge of the matter said. The highest offer was around 50 billion yen ($440 million) in the first round, bankers said and a bank executive said bidders may now offer less than that. [ID:nL4N0SW38A]  ** Minority shareholders in Malaysian Airline System Bhd <MASM.KL> overwhelmingly backed a $421 million offer by its majority owner, state fund Khazanah Nasional Bhd's <KHAZA.UL>, to take the struggling carrier private. [ID:nL4N0SW4WT]  ** U.S. private investment firm Bain Capital is selling $200 million worth of shares in India's Hero MotoCorp Ltd <HROM.NS>, with an option to sell more, according to a term sheet seen by Reuters. [ID:nL4N0SW3I5]  ** Dairy Crest Group Plc <DCG.L>, Britain's largest dairy food company, said it would sell some dairy assets including factories to Müller UK & Ireland Group for 80 million pounds ($127.9 million) to reduce debt. [ID:nL4N0SW3XC]  ** British packaging provider DS Smith Plc <SMDS.L> said it has acquired Spanish corrugated board producer Andopack for about 35 million pounds ($56 million), including debt, as it looks to strengthen its position in Spain and cash in on Andopack's reach in Barcelona and Madrid. [ID:nL4N0SV4RS]  ** British pay-TV group BSkyB <BSY.L> is to own a bigger-than-expected 87 percent of Sky Deutschland AG <SKYDn.DE> once its takeover closes, increasing its leverage but also its future earning power from European expansion. [ID:nL6N0SW23O]  ** India's ONGC Videsh, the overseas investment arm of Oil and Natural Gas Corp <ONGC.NS>, is looking to buy a stake in the assets of Africa-focused exploration company Tullow Oil Plc <TLW.L>, a source with direct knowledge of matter said. [ID:nL4N0SW3ZE]  ** Amsterdam-listed OCI NV <OCI.AS> said it planned to spin off its construction and engineering business and list it on stock markets in Egypt and the United Arab Emirates in the first quarter of 2015. [ID:nL6N0SW1KJ]  ** Oil industry veteran Maurice Dijols pledged quick talks with CAT Oil AG <O2C.DE> management and has only the "best intentions" for the Austrian fracking specialist, his investment vehicle said, breaking its silence on its takeover plans. The remarks come a day after CAT oil appealed to the offshore bidder to reveal its intentions and strategy following its stake purchase that triggered a mandatory offer. [ID:nL6N0SW2G5]  ** Middle East private equity firm Abraaj has bought a majority stake in Southeast Asian food and drink chain Wine Connection, as it looks to capitalise on the growing interest in wine and western food among the region's middle class. [ID:nL4N0SW20M]  ** Italian industrial conglomerate Finmeccanica SpA <SIFI.MI> said it has given bidders for its non-core rail assets a Nov. 17 deadline to present offers and would decide on the sale by the end of the year. [ID:nL6N0SW2S4]  ** Polish broadcaster TVN SA's <TVN.WA> chief financial officer said a sale of the majority stake in the company was unlikely to happen in 2014, but added that he expected about a dozen bidders the stake. [ID:nW8N0S902I] [ID:nW8N0S902J]  ** British utility SSE <SSE.L> agreed to sell some of its shareholding in the Beatrice offshore wind farm to Copenhagen Infrastructure Partners. SSE will own a 50 percent share of the project after the sale, while fund management company CIP will own 25 percent and Repsol will own the rest. [ID:nL6N0SW3GA]  ** Turkey's largest food group Yildiz Holding said it suspended for six months its move to hold a block sale of up to 10 percent of its private equity firm Gozde Girisim <GOZDE.IS>. [ID:nL6N0SW2FV]